dges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Anglicized form of the Gaelic name Donnchadh , also used among people without Scottish connections. This was the name of a 7th-century Scottish saint (abbot of Iona) and two medieval kings of Scotland. The final ‐<i>n</i> in the Anglicized form seems to be the result of confusion with the Gaelic word <i>ceann</i> ‘head’ in the Latinized form <i>Duncanus</i>.  Compare Irish  Donagh ."],"variants":[{"name":"Donnchadh","meanings":["Gaelic: compound of Old Celtic <i>donn</i> ‘brown’ + <i>chadh</i> ‘chief’ or ‘noble’."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Duncan Kirkpatrick was born in 1280, in Scotland, his father, Sir Stephen Kirkpatrick Lord of Closeburn, was 34 and his mother, Lady Isabella de Torthorwald, was 30. He had at least 1 son with Isabel De Torthorwald. He died on 16 June 1323, in his hometown, at the age of 43."},"et":{"1280–16 June 1323":"1280–16. juuni 1323","1276–1340":"1276–1340","1279–1357":"1279–1357","1280–1323":"1280–1323","1280–Female":"1280–Surnud","1323–1425":"1323–1425","1246–1320":"1246–1320","1250–Female":"1250–Surnud","March 1323":"märts 1323","1340":"1340","1250":"1250","1280":"1280","1425":"1425","1357":"1357","1246":"1246","1323":"1323","1279":"1279","Abt 1320":"umbes 1320","1320":"1320","1276":"1276","16 June 1323":"16. juuni 1323","Scotland":"Scotland","Torthorwald, Dumfriesshire, Scotland":"Torthorwald, Dumfriesshire, Scotland"},"fi":{"1280–16 June 1323":"1280–16. kesäkuuta 1323","1276–1340":"1276–1340","1279–1357":"1279–1357","1280–1323":"1280–1323","1280–Female":"1280–Kuollut","1323–1425":"1323–1425","1246–1320":"1246–1320","1250–Female":"1250–Kuollut","March 1323":"maaliskuu 1323","1340":"1340","1250":"1250","1280":"1280","1425":"1425","1357":"1357","1246":"1246","1323":"1323","1279":"1279","Abt 1320":"noin 1320","1320":"1320","1276":"1276","16 June 1323":"16. kesäkuuta 1323","Scotland":"Scotland","Torthorwald, Dumfriesshire, Scotland":"Torthorwald, Dumfriesshire, Scotland"},"fr":{"1280–16 June 1323":"1280–1